@mkArtakMSFT This happened in two independent dotnet 6 blazorwasm projects. The default empty app seems to be working fine regarding hot reload.

Also, I made many attempts to fix the bug, including commenting out some relevant parts of the code, changing configuration files and looking at the dotnet source code to get some context of why this could be happening. I could not figure anything out.
`dotnet watch` would seemingly randomly hang up and crash no matter what I did.

It looks like the fundamental issue is that on a full build, the generated `HotReloadStyles.styles.css` file contains the following import automatically:

```css
@import '_content/ClassLibrary/ClassLibrary.bundle.scp.css';
```

On triggering a hot-reload regeneration of this file, the `@import` is lost and it only shows the other content.

